Expansion performed internally based on codesystem NG Reaction Severity v0.4.0 (CodeSystem)

This value set contains 3 concepts

CodeSystemDisplay (en-US)Definition
  mildhttp://nphcda.gov.ng/ig/fhir/CodeSystem/ng-allergy-severityMildThe allergic reaction involves mild symptoms such as localized redness, itching, or rash, without systemic involvement or need for significant medical intervention.
  moderatehttp://nphcda.gov.ng/ig/fhir/CodeSystem/ng-allergy-severityModerateThe reaction includes more pronounced symptoms like widespread hives, mild breathing difficulty, or swelling that requires medical observation or treatment but is not life-threatening.
  severehttp://nphcda.gov.ng/ig/fhir/CodeSystem/ng-allergy-severitySevereThe reaction is life-threatening or requires urgent medical attention, such as anaphylaxis, severe respiratory distress, or cardiovascular compromise.

Expansion performed internally based on codesystem NG Adverse Event Clinical Status v0.4.0 (CodeSystem)

This value set contains 6 concepts

CodeSystemDisplay (en-US)Definition
  activehttp://nphcda.gov.ng/ig/fhir/CodeSystem/ng-clinical-statusActiveThe clinical condition is currently present, ongoing, or requires active management or monitoring.
  inactivehttp://nphcda.gov.ng/ig/fhir/CodeSystem/ng-clinical-statusInactiveThe clinical condition is no longer present but is not considered resolved; it may recur or requires no current treatment.
  resolvedhttp://nphcda.gov.ng/ig/fhir/CodeSystem/ng-clinical-statusResolvedThe clinical condition has completely resolved and is no longer impacting the patientâ€™s health or requiring further management.
  recoveredhttp://nphcda.gov.ng/ig/fhir/CodeSystem/ng-clinical-statusRecoveredThe individual has recovered fully from the adverse event without any long-term effects or sequelae.
  recovered-with-sequelaehttp://nphcda.gov.ng/ig/fhir/CodeSystem/ng-clinical-statusRecovered with sequelaeThe individual has recovered from the adverse event but with lasting effects, complications, or disabilities.
  deathhttp://nphcda.gov.ng/ig/fhir/CodeSystem/ng-clinical-statusDeathThe adverse event resulted in the death of the individual.
